content:
A pie chart is good for showing the relative shares of different quantities. Use the formatting tab to choose how to configure and label the divisions in your pie chart.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Salesforce Classic (not available in all orgs)
Available in: Group (View Only), Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

USER PERMISSIONS
NEEDED
To create dashboards:	Run Reports AND Create and Customize Dashboards
To edit and delete dashboards that you created:	Run Reports AND Create and Customize Dashboards
To edit and delete dashboards that you created in public folders:	Edit My Dashboards
To edit and delete dashboards that you didn’t create in public folders:	Manage Dashboards in Public Folders
To create, edit, and delete dynamic dashboards:	Manage Dynamic Dashboards

SETTING	DESCRIPTION
Sort Rows By	Choose a sorting element to determine what element you want displayed first in the chart.
Maximum Values Displayed	Set the maximum number of elements to include on the chart.
Legend Position	Choose where to display the legend.
Combine Small Groups into “Others”	Combine groups less than or equal to 3% of the total into a single “Others” wedge. Deselect to show all values individually.
Show Values	Display individual record or group values on the chart.
Show %	Display percentage value for each wedge of pie and donut charts.
Enable Hover	Display values, labels, and percentages when hovering over charts.
Show Total	Display total value for the chart.
title: Formatting Pie and Donut Charts in Salesforce
